data.description: Nestled on a serene tree-lined block in Chester, this charming end-of-row home offers a perfect blend of classic design and modern comfort. The inviting front porch sets the tone, leading to a spacious living room adorned with wood moldings and luxury vinyl plank flooring. Sliding glass doors from the dining room open to a large deck, seamlessly connecting indoor and outdoor spaces. The open kitchen features a breakfast bar and modern appliances.  Upstairs, you’ll find three spacious  bedrooms with plenty of storage and natural light as well as a charming hall bath that boasts a soaking tub and skylight. An enclosed side yard and rear parking area complement the outdoor space. The ample basement adds potential for extra storage. This well maintained home is a great opportunity for a first time homebuyer or an investor looking to add to their rental portfolio.  The home is in a convenient location,  minutes to the Meadowbrook Shopping Center, Crozer Chester Hospital and the Philadelphia Airport.  Close to I-95, making for a quick commute to Philadelphia, Delaware or the bridge to New Jersey.
